HEADWORD: Three-ply
<hw>Three"-ply`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Consisting of
three distinct webs inwrought together in weaving, as cloth or
carpeting; having three strands; threefold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-pointed</ent>⟦br⟧
